      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Human Catastrophe</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Eric A Friedman letter says AIDS epidemic in Africa is responsibility of the public and government, not just pharmaceutical companies (July 8 letters)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''As Devastating Epidemics Increase, Nations Take On Drug Companies'' (news article, July 9):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''As Devastating Epidemics Increase, Nations Take On Drug Companies'' (news article, July 9):</p>
        <p>The focus on the high price of AIDS medication in developing countries makes it seem as if the primary responsibility for saving tens of millions of lives rests in the private hands of the pharmaceutical companies. What is happening in Africa is a responsibility of the public, and we the public should not permit our government to divert attention from its own inexcusable failure to face this human catastrophe.</p>
        <p>ERIC A. FRIEDMAN  Larchmont, N.Y., July 9, 2000</p>
      </block>
